pageContext.description: 3 indistinct raised lines ending in pellets, these are longer on other face. Edge sharp & fine. apparently reground slightly (anciently). Cast marks. smoothed down.
pageContext.patina: patches of patina black & red brown
pageContext.surface: dull golden bronze. fairly smooth. pitted & worn in parts.
pageContext.collection: Private Collection 1923, Colonel Francis R. Twemlow DSO. J.J. FSA. Peatswood (Staffs), Market Drayton.
pageContext.site: England, Shropshire, Market Drayton, Broomhall Grange Farm, near Shropshire bank of R. Tern, between Hinsley Mill & Shifford's Bridge, About 1913. by an estate man, about 3 feet down, while digging drain, in a hollow which had the appearance of being an old watercourse.
